---

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium
heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to
> an ovenproof dish before baking.

Add the @risotto rice{175%grams}. Stir and cook, ~{1-2%mins}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{20%grams}, @tomato puree{30%grams} and
@boiled water{600%milliliters}. Bring to the boil. Pop a lid on the pan
(or cover with foil) and bake on the middle shelf, ~{25-30%mins}.

When the risotto has 10 mins remaining, bake the @demi garlic baguettes{2} in
the oven, ~{10-15%mins}.

Meanwhile, drain the @king prawns{225%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the prawns, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%mins}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they
> they're opaque in the middle.

When the rice is cooked, remove it from the oven. Mix in the @peas{120%grams},
prawns, @vegan 'nduja{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder),
@butter{20%grams} and two thirds of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{60%grams}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water to
loosen the rice if needed.

Share between your #bowls{} and sprinkle over the remaining cheese.

Serve the garlic baguettes alongside.

Enjoy!